A MPUMALANGA school burnt down after it was allegedly struck by lighting in the early hours of yesterday morning. All the classrooms on the second floor at Barberton Secondary School were completely destroyed. The Department of Education confirmed to Daily Sun that the school was destroyed by fire. But spokesman Jasper Zwane couldn’t confirm the cause of the fire. A team of experts from the infrastructure directorate was sent to the school to assess damage and compile a report. “Everything possible will be done to ensure this does not affect reopening in January,” said Zwane. This is the ninth school to be destroyed by fire in the province this year. “Eight of the schools in various areas were allegedly burned down by protesters.